I thought about telling you all about what happened to me whenever I was always upset.

00:32:34.480 --> 00:32:34.880
I know there's a lot of you that have heard this, but there's some that have not.

00:32:34.880 --> 00:32:40.880
So, I will tell you about the time when Jesus visited me.

00:32:40.880 --> 00:32:43.760
This was a visitation; it was real.

00:32:43.760 --> 00:32:46.100
It wasn't a dream.

00:32:46.100 --> 00:32:49.280
This wasn't a vision.

00:32:49.280 --> 00:32:52.120
He actually came to my house.

00:33:01.699 --> 00:33:02.159
And there's some of you who say, 'I don't believe it at all.

00:33:02.159 --> 00:33:04.740
' But that's fine.

00:33:04.740 --> 00:33:08.343
I'll tell you what happened.

00:33:19.700 --> 00:33:30.400
I was in bed and all of a sudden I felt a hand touch me and he woke me up out of my sleep.

00:33:30.400 --> 00:33:39.413
Before my bed I was laying there on this side right here.

00:33:45.919 --> 00:33:58.312
I was laying like this and he touched this side of my shoulder and he touched me and I woke up and I looked up and Jesus was standing there and he said, 'I've come to give you your request.

00:34:02.000 --> 00:34:02.958
I want to show you something.

00:34:02.958 --> 00:34:10.056
' And all of a sudden the floor began to glow.

00:34:10.056 --> 00:34:37.440
It opened up in a portal before me and I was taken back at this so much as you are in the natural like flesh and I'm seeing all this and my floor is breathing.

00:34:37.440 --> 00:34:47.550
It started to open up in this portal and it was turning and it was breathing and it was accelerating.

00:35:03.111 --> 00:35:03.307
It was exhaling, inhaling, and it was moving all around my floor.

00:35:31.406 --> 00:35:31.680
And he said, 'Put your feet over here.

00:35:31.680 --> 00:35:40.057
' And he goes, 'Jump.

00:35:40.057 --> 00:35:45.920
' So I took my feet and I said, 'You want me to jump?

00:35:45.920 --> 00:35:50.743
' He said, 'Trust me, Brandon.

00:35:50.743 --> 00:35:52.823
' I said, 'Of course, Lord.

00:35:52.823 --> 00:35:58.708
' I took my feet and I fell inside of that portal.

00:36:06.859 --> 00:36:07.359
It was moving and breathing and I was instantaneously taken to my past.

00:36:11.063 --> 00:36:12.380
And I went to the hospital where my little girl got her shots.

00:36:12.380 --> 00:36:24.728
And he said, 'Brandon, you've asked me and asked me to have the opportunity in your heart to have a second chance to tell yourself not to give Megan the flu shot.

00:36:29.664 --> 00:36:29.952
I'm going to give you that request.

00:36:29.952 --> 00:36:35.760
' And all of a sudden he said, 'Go now.

00:36:35.760 --> 00:36:40.427
You're about to do it.

00:36:40.427 --> 00:36:47.131
' I ran and I could see the hospital room.

00:36:59.680 --> 00:37:00.480
I knew it was on the fourth floor.

00:37:06.304 --> 00:37:06.608
I ran all the way up the stairs.

00:37:09.040 --> 00:37:13.085
I busted through the doctor's office and I saw the nurse about ready to give Megan the vaccination.

00:37:14.526 --> 00:37:27.822
And at me as a young man and my wife was sitting there and we were watching our daughter about to get this flu shot, I said, 'Stop.

00:37:27.822 --> 00:37:29.200
Don't do it.

00:37:29.200 --> 00:37:39.333
' And all of a sudden, that nurse took that thing back and did not administer that and a scream came before my face.

00:37:57.531 --> 00:37:57.909
And every single year was planned out in front of me from where I was to the present.

00:38:06.497 --> 00:38:06.808
And now this has been years ago.

00:38:06.808 --> 00:38:15.349
And this is just out of my memory of everything that happened.

00:38:15.359 --> 00:38:16.660
So if I miss anything, forgive me.

00:38:16.660 --> 00:38:32.150
But I remember I saw it play out and Jesus stood right there and he said, 'Now I want to show you the power of a decision.

00:38:32.160 --> 00:38:38.286
Watch what happens now with your life because of that vaccination or what would change.

00:38:38.286 --> 00:38:42.194
' Megan was already developed.

00:38:42.194 --> 00:38:45.040
She was already starting to talk.

00:38:45.040 --> 00:38:47.080
She was totally normal.

00:38:47.080 --> 00:38:49.850
Her Apgar scores were completely normal.

00:38:49.850 --> 00:38:52.312
But as that did not happen, I was a bad person.

00:38:52.312 --> 00:38:53.240
I was very angry.

00:38:58.187 --> 00:38:58.987
I was very verbally abusive to my wife all the time.

00:38:59.787 --> 00:39:01.006
I talked down to her.

00:39:01.006 --> 00:39:03.140
I didn't treat her right.

00:39:03.140 --> 00:39:04.400
I was very hard-hearted.

00:39:04.400 --> 00:39:06.891
I was very angry at the finances.

00:39:06.891 --> 00:39:12.658
Where we were financially, I was very bitter towards a lot of things.

00:39:15.680 --> 00:39:23.200
But the moment Megan didn't get that and change didn't happen, I saw my life without the pressure of autism is what I'm trying to tell y'all.

00:39:23.760 --> 00:39:24.560
Megan developed normally.

00:39:26.160 --> 00:39:26.467
Everything was normal.

00:39:26.467 --> 00:39:28.390
But I didn't change.

00:39:28.390 --> 00:39:31.119
I became even more hard.

00:39:50.942 --> 00:39:51.084
And Diana and I drifted apart.

00:39:51.653 --> 00:40:00.183
I saw the year that Diana left me and she moved back home to Texas to be with her mama and she filed for a divorce.

00:40:18.710 --> 00:40:18.960
I saw it all play right in front of my face in a movie screen of all the power of a choice because what didn't change me was my daughter's special needs.

00:40:20.960 --> 00:40:23.138
I saw it all pan out in front of me.

00:40:23.138 --> 00:40:29.839
I saw when Diana left; she got remarried to a man that was pretty wealthy.

00:40:30.132 --> 00:40:33.140
I saw Megan on the weekends every other week.

00:40:34.973 --> 00:40:35.707
I became even more angry.

00:40:35.707 --> 00:40:39.120
Her life was better.

00:40:39.120 --> 00:40:39.840
Mine wasn't.

00:40:42.300 --> 00:40:42.600
I didn't get remarried.

00:40:45.890 --> 00:40:48.480
I was very angry—heavier than what I am now.

00:40:51.429 --> 00:40:59.804
He said, "I want to show you now: your son won't be born and there's a call on his life, and here in the future you'll have a little girl.

00:40:59.804 --> 00:41:09.810
You'll have a little girl, and she won't be born either, and she has a major call in her life too.

00:41:09.810 --> 00:41:11.387
" He said, "Brandon...

00:41:21.200 --> 00:41:27.330
" He started preaching to me and he started talking to me about everything—to sum it up and not make this really long for y'all tonight because I'm already going over.

00:41:27.330 --> 00:41:36.710
But he said, "Brandon, I didn't cause Megan to have autism.

00:41:41.509 --> 00:41:41.699
I did not do this to you to teach you anything.

00:41:49.420 --> 00:41:49.680
" He said to me, "The devil comes to kill, steal, and destroy.

00:41:55.813 --> 00:41:56.080
But what the devil meant for bad, I'll turn it around for good in your favor.

00:41:56.080 --> 00:42:02.436
You're not big enough to mess up your life.

00:42:02.436 --> 00:42:06.377
You're not big enough to mess up your life, Brandon.

00:42:06.377 --> 00:42:17.706
No matter how many bad choices you've made, he said, 'As long as the footsteps of the righteous are ordered of the Lord.

00:42:17.706 --> 00:42:25.220
And as long as you're right with me and you're seeking me, I'll turn it around.

00:42:25.220 --> 00:42:39.634
I'll turn what the devil meant for bad, Brandon, and I'll turn it around for good in your favor as long as you're looking towards me.

00:42:39.634 --> 00:42:43.880
'" Because in my mind, I always told him, "I can't do ministry.

00:42:48.280 --> 00:42:48.650
I can't lay hands on the sick.

00:42:49.390 --> 00:42:53.279
I can't do all that because of Megan, Lord.

00:42:53.279 --> 00:43:00.766
What do you call me to healing ministry?

00:43:00.766 --> 00:43:03.943
Well, you called me to do all these things.

00:43:03.943 --> 00:43:07.630
I'm broken because of this.

00:43:07.630 --> 00:43:14.560
" But he said, "Brandon, Megan does not validate my word.

00:43:14.560 --> 00:43:16.697
My word validates itself.

00:43:16.697 --> 00:43:18.640
It's a pillar.

00:43:18.640 --> 00:43:23.387
Megan's healing doesn't validate that I'm a healer.

00:43:23.387 --> 00:43:26.416
My word validates that.

00:43:26.416 --> 00:43:34.183
" As he said all these things to me, I saw the pressure from having a child with special needs.

00:43:34.183 --> 00:43:58.040
As I was ready to drive off a bridge, as I was ready to do away with myself so many different times, as I was driving home and crying behind the toilets, cleaning the church bathrooms, and doing all the things that I went through being a janitor for 15 years—it molded me.

00:43:58.040 --> 00:44:13.611
It took a really hard heart and made it soft as I had to buckle up and honor my wife and go through this very hard time raising a child with special needs.

00:44:29.804 --> 00:44:30.008
The pressure on the potter's wheel makes you different if you yield to it.

00:44:38.336 --> 00:44:39.008
It's the pressure.

00:44:39.008 --> 00:44:48.559
We have this treasure in earthen vessels that the excellency of the power will be known to him and not of us.

00:44:52.800 --> 00:44:57.640
But the pressure from Megan and all the things that I went through made me into who I am today.

00:44:57.640 --> 00:45:09.180
As he kept telling me that I couldn't mess my life up no matter how bad I've done things in the past, he said, "I told you if the footsteps of the righteous are ordered of the Lord.

00:45:09.180 --> 00:45:10.420
" He encouraged me.

00:45:10.420 --> 00:45:12.411
He preached to me.

00:45:12.411 --> 00:45:17.141
He preached a really fiery message that I wish I could remember all of it.

00:45:17.141 --> 00:45:19.610
I've never heard Jesus as a preacher.

00:45:24.148 --> 00:45:24.422
And boy, he could preach fire.

00:45:24.422 --> 00:45:26.280
I'll never forget it.

00:45:26.280 --> 00:45:36.343
I sat there and watched him as he preached to me, and he told me that I had a call on my life and he wanted me to do something for him.

00:45:36.343 --> 00:45:57.508
I thought at that moment that I had totally derailed my life because of what the doctor had told us: that Megan would never be normal and that she would never be potty trained.

00:45:57.508 --> 00:46:07.656
She would never have a normal life, and we'd be lucky if she ever gets out of an 18-month-old's stage.

00:46:07.656 --> 00:46:15.280
But that's why I've tried to tell you all over and over again.

00:46:33.700 --> 00:46:33.970
Right now, we weren't able to do anything.

00:46:33.970 --> 00:46:38.570
If anybody realized how bad Megan was—she would urinate on everything.

00:46:39.227 --> 00:46:42.194
She would play with her feces every day.

00:46:54.331 --> 00:46:54.560
She would bite herself until blood would run down her hands, pull her hair out.

00:46:54.560 --> 00:47:10.011
She had huge bald spots all over her head where she'd pull all her hair out, take everything out of one drawer in one room and put it in there.

00:47:10.011 --> 00:47:12.450
I never knew where my toothbrush was.

00:47:12.450 --> 00:47:15.737
I never knew where my deodorant was.

00:47:15.737 --> 00:47:20.266
I never knew where my soap from my bathroom was.

00:47:20.266 --> 00:47:34.610
She'd take all the ornaments off the tree every single year and put them in the kitchen sink.

00:47:34.610 --> 00:47:36.720
We never could have a Christmas tree.

00:47:36.720 --> 00:47:38.639
We never could do anything.

00:47:38.639 --> 00:47:40.880
We did that for years.

00:47:45.800 --> 00:47:46.170
And then one day Jesus visited us.

00:47:54.359 --> 00:47:59.359
And in that time whenever he visited, I was at the sink and I was complaining, and I said to him, "You don't hear anything I'm saying?

00:47:59.359 --> 00:48:05.180
I prayed and prayed and prayed for her to get better.

00:48:17.520 --> 00:48:17.853
" And I said, "She's not.

00:48:33.1000 --> 00:48:34.400
Do you hear, and have you heard, any of my prayers?

00:48:40.360 --> 00:48:40.750
" I was washing the dishes.

00:48:40.750 --> 00:48:49.840
And at that time, the glory of the Lord filled my whole house.

00:48:49.840 --> 00:48:51.980
And I saw him visibly again.

00:48:53.813 --> 00:48:54.372
I was on the floor and Diana couldn't see him.

00:48:59.973 --> 00:49:00.200
I was on the floor and he melted me like wax.

00:49:04.939 --> 00:49:05.119
I thought I was going to die.

00:49:09.164 --> 00:49:14.354
The presence of the Lord was so strong in my house; I thought I was going to die.

00:49:14.354 --> 00:49:27.688
I looked up at him and I said, "Jesus, don't you know what I've asked for?

00:49:27.688 --> 00:49:35.680
" Because he asked me, the first thing he asked me was, "What do you have need of?

00:49:39.184 --> 00:49:39.432
" I said, "Don't you know what I have need of?

00:49:39.432 --> 00:49:39.897
Megan!

00:49:39.897 --> 00:49:47.737
" He said, "According to your faith, be it done unto you, Brandon.

00:49:47.737 --> 00:49:50.960
According to your faith, be it done unto you.

00:49:50.960 --> 00:50:05.223
" Diana came around the corner at this time and she saw me on the floor and she felt the presence of the Lord so strong in the house and she thought I was dying.

00:50:05.223 --> 00:50:06.420
She started screaming.

00:50:06.420 --> 00:50:10.499
She says, "Jesus, don't take him.

00:50:10.499 --> 00:50:12.259
Don't take him.

00:50:17.440 --> 00:50:17.624
I need my husband.

00:50:17.624 --> 00:50:19.280
I can't do this on my own.

00:50:19.280 --> 00:50:21.599
" She goes, "Is he dying?

00:50:21.599 --> 00:50:22.422
Are you dying?

00:50:24.400 --> 00:50:24.853
" And she started yelling.

00:50:26.071 --> 00:50:27.626
I said, "Jesus is here, honey.

00:50:27.626 --> 00:50:33.848
" She says, "I know, I can feel it, but I can't see him.

00:50:34.880 --> 00:50:43.650
" And I started crying out and he ministered to me and he put his hand on my head and he blessed me.

00:50:43.650 --> 00:50:47.564
He said, "She'll start to amend from this hour.

00:50:51.314 --> 00:50:54.900
" And I knew it's going to be gradual like I've always told y'all; a miracle is a miracle even if it's not overnight.

00:50:54.900 --> 00:50:57.546
A miracle is a miracle even if it's progressive.

00:50:58.613 --> 00:51:02.834
I saw everything from that day forward—that I knew it was going to be a journey.

00:51:02.834 --> 00:51:12.053
But Jesus told me, "According to your faith, be it done unto you.

00:51:12.053 --> 00:51:23.359
" When I woke up the next day, I went over and told my grandfather because we lived across the street at the time.

00:51:23.359 --> 00:51:28.360
I said, "Grandpa, we had a visitation from Jesus.

00:51:28.360 --> 00:51:30.000
" Megan didn't act any different.

00:51:39.850 --> 00:51:40.102
I thought, "Surely if Jesus shows up in your house, Megan's going to be completely healed and it's going to be a sign and a wonder.

00:51:40.102 --> 00:51:41.108
" Time goes by.

00:51:41.108 --> 00:51:54.987
This is a Friday, Saturday, Sunday, Monday—she goes to her little ABA therapy lady and she calls and she said, "Brandon, what happened to Megan?

00:51:56.434 --> 00:51:57.531
" I said, "Kimberly, what are you talking about?

00:52:03.280 --> 00:52:03.680
What happened to Megan?

00:52:03.680 --> 00:52:07.460
" She said, "Something's happened to Megan.

00:52:21.280 --> 00:52:21.568
" I said, "What?

00:52:21.568 --> 00:52:22.144
What?

00:52:22.144 --> 00:52:24.160
Does she have a bruise?

00:52:24.160 --> 00:52:26.720
What is it?

00:52:26.720 --> 00:52:31.719
" Because you're thinking, "What are you accusing me of?

00:52:35.599 --> 00:52:35.919
" But it wasn't.

00:52:35.919 --> 00:52:39.910
She said, "She's saying little sentences.

00:52:39.910 --> 00:52:43.580
She's parroting something for the first time.

00:52:43.580 --> 00:52:44.150
Something's happened.

00:52:44.150 --> 00:52:45.980
" She was saying red; she says blue.

00:52:45.980 --> 00:52:51.440
She says all these different colors that she was parroting from that day forward.

00:53:12.960 --> 00:53:13.138
And Megan still does those things.

00:53:13.138 --> 00:53:15.189
She even told me today, "Hi, daddy, mommy.

00:53:15.189 --> 00:53:17.017
" She was talking to both of us.

00:53:17.017 --> 00:53:23.808
But from that time forward, it's been a step all the time and we keep seeing a little bit more.

00:53:29.980 --> 00:53:30.250
But then, even my family, nobody could even touch her hardly.

00:53:30.250 --> 00:53:33.459
She acted like she was a wild animal.

00:53:33.459 --> 00:53:35.732
It was absolutely hell on earth.

00:53:49.620 --> 00:53:49.810
But from that time forward when Jesus visited, she's gotten better and better.

00:53:51.750 --> 00:53:52.600
And it hasn't been instantaneous, like everything's better.

00:53:52.600 --> 00:53:57.050
Like the one with the issue of blood, I'm believing that moment's coming.

00:53:58.346 --> 00:54:01.297
But what I'm trying to tell you is that sometimes it's progressive.

00:54:01.297 --> 00:54:10.186
Now, between that and all that I've told you of two visitations tonight and just that short little bit of time, I cut them up in pieces to make that really quick for you.

00:54:10.186 --> 00:54:13.989
What I'm trying to tell you is I want you to believe God for it.

00:54:13.989 --> 00:54:30.400
No matter how bad you think you've disrupted your life and you think that you can't be used by God, and no matter how hard you think you've had it, the footsteps of the righteous are ordered by the Lord, and you're not big enough to derail your life.

00:54:30.880 --> 00:54:32.914
You can say, 'Well, Brandon, I was a prostitute.

00:54:39.528 --> 00:54:39.824
I was on drugs.

00:54:39.824 --> 00:54:41.599
I was in jail.

00:54:42.920 --> 00:54:48.091
I went and I did, I robbed banks.

00:54:48.091 --> 00:54:54.133
' Or maybe you're a wife beater.

00:54:54.133 --> 00:54:58.669
Maybe you were all these different things and your wife left you or whatever.

00:54:58.669 --> 00:55:18.613
But what I'm trying to tell you is that no matter how bad you think you are, no matter how bad you've disrupted your life, if you're seeking God, no matter how bad you've messed up, God will turn it on a dime.

00:55:18.613 --> 00:55:21.539
Never give up on what your dreams are.

00:55:21.539 --> 00:55:24.319
Never give up on what you're believing for.

00:55:24.319 --> 00:55:29.550
Always stay close to the vine.

00:55:29.550 --> 00:55:40.293
Regardless of how hard you think your life is, it's the pressure that changes you.

00:55:51.712 --> 00:55:51.936
You may have been a janitor.

00:56:03.600 --> 00:56:03.800
You may have been a store clerk.

00:56:03.800 --> 00:56:08.292
You may be somebody that was a gas attendant.

00:56:08.292 --> 00:56:10.106
It doesn't matter.

00:56:10.106 --> 00:56:18.133
Whatever you do, in word and in deed, do all to the glory of God.

00:56:18.133 --> 00:56:22.187
God will promote you in due time.

00:56:33.702 --> 00:56:34.011
It takes time sometimes because we have a lot of flesh in the way.

00:56:34.011 --> 00:56:42.240
In my circumstances, being a janitor for 15 years and having a child still right now that's overcoming...

00:56:42.240 --> 00:56:48.514
As we were driving home tonight, she was quiet.

00:56:55.168 --> 00:56:55.376
I said, 'Megan's okay.

00:56:55.584 --> 00:56:56.832
You want an ice cream?

00:56:56.832 --> 00:56:59.359
' So I went by and got her an ice cream.

00:57:08.319 --> 00:57:11.119
I thought about that a lot as we go through this Christmas season because I dread holidays a lot going around family.

00:57:11.369 --> 00:57:14.471
You think, 'Well, how is she going to act?

00:57:14.471 --> 00:57:16.800
How things are going?

00:57:16.800 --> 00:57:26.311
' But I can tell you Jesus has brought us so far even at Christmas time.

00:57:26.311 --> 00:57:40.039
So I don't know what you're going through tonight, but I try to just give you a little bit of encouragement to keep on keeping on.

00:57:40.039 --> 00:57:42.399
Don't be weary in well-doing.

00:57:42.399 --> 00:57:46.079
Don't be weary in well-doing in your job.

00:57:52.426 --> 00:57:53.666
And know that if you're on the potter's wheel, he always finishes a perfect product.

00:57:53.666 --> 00:57:57.303
There's no mistakes.

00:57:57.303 --> 00:58:01.419
There's no mistakes with the Father.

00:58:05.964 --> 00:58:06.276
You might be a rich billionaire.

00:58:10.810 --> 00:58:15.360
You might be watching this and you're worth hundreds of millions of dollars, but you're still a work in progress.

00:58:15.360 --> 00:58:24.480
No matter how much money you have, Jesus Christ loves you and he paid the price for you.

00:58:36.480 --> 00:58:36.880
He has a plan for your life.

00:58:36.880 --> 00:58:46.560
No matter how much depression you could be overcoming and everybody thinks you have it all together driving a Ferrari or whatever.

00:58:46.560 --> 00:59:02.880
I've noticed that there's a lot of people who have money that have it all that are the most depressed, saddest people with broken marriages more than anybody else.

00:59:20.240 --> 00:59:20.460
But I'm trying to tell you it's not about money.

00:59:20.460 --> 00:59:22.270
It's not about not having money.

00:59:22.270 --> 00:59:36.816
It's about seeking Jesus and having a relationship with him, and he'll turn your life around even whenever you feel like you're in the deepest, darkest hole if you just yield yourself over and say, 'Jesus, I need you.

00:59:45.440 --> 00:59:45.704
I can't do this on my own.

00:59:45.704 --> 00:59:51.133
' I'm so thankful that I yielded to the process of the potter's wheel.

00:59:51.133 --> 00:59:52.780
I'm not a finished work.

00:59:52.780 --> 00:59:55.960
I'm still on that potter's wheel every single day.

00:59:55.960 --> 00:59:58.107
I'm a work in progress.

01:00:09.400 --> 01:00:09.626
